commit 1f3ed5c7b64bc1850a6c4bc2c21c09e26cb469af
Author: Sebastian Utz <su@rtme.net>
Date:   Tue Mar 18 17:21:58 2025 +0100

    Fix NPE queries on `sys.allocations` if no master is discovered
    
    If the master is not discovered, `getMasterNodeId()` will
    return NULL which causes the `forTableOnSingleNode` to fail.
    
    Adding a new `Routing.forMasterNode()` method which catches this
    and throws the related exceptions fixes this.
    
    (cherry picked from commit aeddddeba6a7f487891cc8b131fc87bfdf157623)

